# shadcn/ui Dialog Component Guidelines

## Standard Dialog Pattern
- **ALWAYS Use Standard Props**
  - Dialog components MUST use `open` and `onOpenChange` props
  - DO NOT change these to custom names like `isOpen`, `onClose`
  - Follow shadcn/ui standard patterns consistently
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Standard Dialog pattern
  interface DialogProps {
    open: boolean;
    onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void;
  }
  
  export function MyDialog({ open, onOpenChange }: DialogProps) {
    return (
      <Dialog open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
        <DialogContent>
          <Button onClick={() => onOpenChange(false)}>Close</Button>
        </DialogContent>
      </Dialog>
    );
  }

  // ❌ DON'T: Custom prop names
  interface DialogProps {
    isOpen: boolean;     // Wrong: should be 'open'
    onClose: () => void; // Wrong: should be 'onOpenChange'
  }
  ```

- **Proper Dialog Usage in Components**
  - When using Dialog components, pass the correct callback format
  - Handle both opening and closing states properly
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Correct Dialog usage
  const [isDialogOpen, setIsDialogOpen] = useState(false);
  
  <MyDialog 
    open={isDialogOpen}
    onOpenChange={(open) => !open && setIsDialogOpen(false)}
  />

  // ❌ DON'T: Incorrect callback patterns
  <MyDialog 
    isOpen={isDialogOpen}                    // Wrong prop name
    onClose={() => setIsDialogOpen(false)}   // Wrong prop name
  />
  ```

## Dialog Form Patterns
- **Form Dialogs Should Close on Success**
  - Use `onOpenChange(false)` after successful form submission
  - Handle form reset and state cleanup properly
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Proper form dialog pattern
  const onSubmit = async (data) => {
    try {
      await submitForm(data);
      toast.success("성공했습니다");
      onOpenChange(false); // Close dialog on success
    } catch (error) {
      toast.error("실패했습니다");
    }
  };

  // ❌ DON'T: Using non-standard close methods
  const onSubmit = async (data) => {
    await submitForm(data);
    onClose(); // Wrong: should be onOpenChange(false)
  };
  ```

## Critical Rule: Never Change Standard Component Interfaces
- **NEVER modify shadcn/ui component prop interfaces**
  - These are established patterns used across the entire codebase
  - Changing them breaks consistency and causes type errors
  - When fixing type errors, check if you're using the wrong prop names first
  - Reference existing working examples before creating new patterns

# Login and Session Management Guidelines

## Authentication Implementation

### Session Management
- **Use Lightweight Session Storage**
  - Store minimal user data in localStorage
  - Include only essential fields: employeeId, name, role
  - Avoid storing sensitive data
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Minimal session data
  const session = {
    employeeId: "EMP123",
    name: "John Doe",
    role: "employee"
  };

  // ❌ DON'T: Excessive session data
  const session = {
    employeeId: "EMP123",
    name: "John Doe",
    password: "hashedPassword", // Never store sensitive data
    lastLogin: "timestamp",     // Unnecessary session data
    preferences: {}            // Non-essential data
  };
  ```

### Form Validation
- **Use Zod with Korean Error Messages**
  - Define schemas in `src/lib/validations/schemas.ts`
  - Include Korean error messages for better UX
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Korean error messages
  const loginSchema = z.object({
    employeeId: z.string().min(1, "사번을 입력해주세요"),
    name: z.string().min(1, "이름을 입력해주세요"),
  });

  // ❌ DON'T: English or missing error messages
  const loginSchema = z.object({
    employeeId: z.string().min(1, "Employee ID required"),
    name: z.string().min(1),  // Missing error message
  });
  ```

### Auth Guard Pattern
- **Implement Route Protection**
  - Use custom hooks for auth checks
  - Redirect unauthenticated users to login
  - Handle loading states appropriately
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Proper auth guard
  export function useAuthGuard() {
    const router = useRouter();
    const { user, isLoading } = useAuthStore();

    useEffect(() => {
      if (!isLoading && !user) {
        router.replace("/login");
      }
    }, [user, isLoading, router]);

    return { isLoading, user };
  }
  ```

## Toast Notifications
- **Standardize User Feedback**
  - Use toast for all auth-related feedback
  - Keep messages concise and actionable
  - Include success and error states
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Clear, actionable messages
  toast.success("로그인되었습니다");
  toast.error("로그인에 실패했습니다. 다시 시도해주세요");

  // ❌ DON'T: Vague or technical messages
  toast.error("Authentication failed: Error 401");
  ```

## Component Structure
- **Login Form Organization**
  - Keep form logic in custom hooks
  - Separate validation from UI
  - Use proper form labeling for accessibility
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Proper component structure
  export function LoginForm() {
    const { register, handleSubmit, errors } = useLoginForm();
    
    return (
      <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
        <Label htmlFor="employeeId">사번</Label>
        <Input
          id="employeeId"
          {...register("employeeId")}
          aria-describedby="employeeId-error"
        />
        {errors.employeeId && (
          <span id="employeeId-error" className="text-red-500">
            {errors.employeeId.message}
          </span>
        )}
      </form>
    );
  }
  ```

## Metadata and SEO
- **Page-specific Metadata**
  - Include relevant Korean titles and descriptions
  - Set appropriate viewport settings
  - Use proper character encoding
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Proper metadata
  export const metadata = {
    title: "로그인 | 회의실 예약 시스템",
    description: "회의실 예약 시스템 로그인 페이지입니다",
  };

  // ❌ DON'T: Missing or incomplete metadata
  export const metadata = {
    title: "Login",  // Missing Korean title
  };
  ```

## Error Handling
- **Graceful Error Management**
  - Handle network errors appropriately
  - Provide user-friendly error messages
  - Log errors for debugging
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Proper error handling
  try {
    await login(data);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Login error:", error);
    toast.error("로그인에 실패했습니다. 잠시 후 다시 시도해주세요");
  }

  // ❌ DON'T: Poor error handling
  try {
    await login(data);
  } catch (error) {
    alert(error.message);  // Don't use alert
  }
  ``` 
