### **Meeting Room Booking System: MVP Specification**

## 1\. Overview

This document defines the core database schema and data flow for the Minimum Viable Product (MVP) version of the "Simple Meeting Room Booker" tool. It is based on Supabase PostgreSQL and focuses on the rapid and stable implementation of core features.

**Implementation Status**: ✅ **COMPLETED**
- Database migration: `supabase/migrations/00000000000001_complete_schema.sql` (통합 마이그레이션)
- TypeScript types: `src/types/database.ts`
- Service layer: `src/lib/services/`
- State management: `src/lib/store/`
- React hooks: `src/hooks/`
- Validation schemas: `src/lib/validations/schemas.ts`
- Utilities: `src/lib/utils/date.ts`
- **✅ QR Authentication**: 완전 구현됨
- **✅ Cancellation Reason**: 완전 구현됨
- **✅ Authentication Integration**: auth_id 필드로 Supabase Auth 연동

## 2\. Business Requirements (MVP)

### 2.1 Core Entities

  - **Users**: Employees and Administrators with authentication support.
  - **Rooms**: Bookable spaces.
  - **Reservations**: Information about room bookings with cancellation tracking.
  - **QR Login Sessions**: QR code authentication sessions.

### 2.2 Key Business Rules (MVP)

  - Prevent double-booking for the same room and time.
  - Real-time synchronization for creating, updating, and canceling reservations.
  - Administrators have full management rights over all reservations.
  - **NEW**: QR code authentication for mobile access.
  - **NEW**: Cancellation reason tracking for audit purposes.

## 3\. Data Flow Design (MVP)

### 3.1 Simplified Reservation Creation Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant C as Client
    participant API as tRPC API
    participant DB as Supabase DB
    participant RT as Realtime

    U->>C: Fills out reservation form
    C->>API: createReservation(data)
    API->>DB: Check for duplicates (SELECT)
    DB-->>API: Check result
    alt No conflict
        API->>DB: INSERT reservation
        DB-->>API: Reservation created
        DB->>RT: CDC event broadcast
        RT-->>C: Real-time update
        API-->>C: Success response
    else Conflict exists
        API-->>C: Error response
    end
```

