## 6\. Updated Public Reservation Function

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION get_public_reservations(start_date timestamptz, end_date timestamptz)
RETURNS TABLE (
    id uuid,
    room_id uuid,
    user_id uuid,
    title text,
    purpose text,
    department text,
    start_time timestamptz,
    end_time timestamptz,
    is_mine boolean
)
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
AS $$
BEGIN
    RETURN QUERY
    SELECT
        r.id,
        r.room_id,
        r.user_id,
        CASE
            WHEN r.user_id = (SELECT id FROM users WHERE auth_id = auth.uid()) THEN r.title
            ELSE 'Booked'
        END AS title,
        CASE
            WHEN r.user_id = (SELECT id FROM users WHERE auth_id = auth.uid()) THEN r.purpose
            ELSE NULL
        END AS purpose,
        u.department,
        r.start_time,
        r.end_time,
        (r.user_id = (SELECT id FROM users WHERE auth_id = auth.uid())) as is_mine
    FROM reservations r
    JOIN users u ON r.user_id = u.id
    WHERE
        r.status = 'confirmed' AND
        r.start_time < end_date AND
        r.end_time > start_date;
END;
$$;
```

**주요 변경사항:**
- `auth.uid()` 대신 `auth_id` 기반 사용자 식별
- 더 안정적인 사용자 매칭

