# Requirements Document

## Introduction

The Next.js application is experiencing a "ReferenceError: self is not defined" error during build process. The error occurs at `.next/server/vendors-55776fae.js:1:14`, indicating that browser-specific code (using the `self` global object) is being incorrectly bundled into the server-side code. The `self` object exists only in browser/Web Worker environments, not in Node.js server environment. The system needs to identify and isolate the problematic client-side code from server-side bundles without modifying the existing application architecture.

## Requirements

### Requirement 1

**User Story:** As a developer, I want the Next.js build process to complete without "self is not defined" errors, so that I can run the application successfully.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN the build process runs THEN the system SHALL not include browser-specific code in server bundles
2. WHEN server-side rendering occurs THEN the system SHALL not reference browser globals like `self`
3. WHEN the application builds THEN the system SHALL properly separate client and server code

### Requirement 2

**User Story:** As a developer, I want proper module system configuration, so that all dependencies work correctly together.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN TypeScript files are processed THEN the system SHALL use consistent ES module syntax
2. WHEN JavaScript configuration files are processed THEN the system SHALL use appropriate module formats
3. WHEN third-party dependencies are imported THEN the system SHALL resolve modules without conflicts

### Requirement 3

**User Story:** As a developer, I want clear error diagnostics, so that I can identify and fix module issues quickly.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN module errors occur THEN the system SHALL provide clear error messages with file locations
2. WHEN configuration issues exist THEN the system SHALL indicate which files need attention
3. WHEN dependencies have conflicts THEN the system SHALL identify problematic packages

### Requirement 4

**User Story:** As a developer, I want the build system to be optimized, so that development and production builds work reliably.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. WHEN webpack processes modules THEN the system SHALL handle both CommonJS and ES modules correctly
2. WHEN Next.js compiles the application THEN the system SHALL maintain consistent module resolution
3. WHEN the application runs in production THEN the system SHALL work without module-related errors
</file>

